<%# First-touch vs last-touch credit by channel — same conversions, two methods. Illustrative numbers. %>

<%
  channels = [
    { name: "Paid Social",     first: 35, last: 8,  role: "introducer" },
    { name: "Display",         first: 18, last: 4,  role: "introducer" },
    { name: "Content / Blog",  first: 22, last: 6,  role: "introducer" },
    { name: "Email",           first: 5,  last: 28, role: "closer" },
    { name: "Retargeting",     first: 2,  last: 18, role: "closer" },
    { name: "Branded Search",  first: 4,  last: 24, role: "closer" },
    { name: "Direct",          first: 14, last: 12, role: "mixed" }
  ]
%>

<figure class="my-12 not-prose">
  <div class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">

    <div class="px-6 sm:px-8 pt-8 pb-6 border-b border-slate-200">
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 tracking-tight">Same conversions. Two ways to assign credit.</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm sm:text-base mt-1">First-touch reveals introducers. Last-touch reveals closers. Same channels &mdash; very different rankings.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="px-4 sm:px-8 py-6 bg-gradient-to-b from-slate-50/60 to-white">

      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-x-5 gap-y-1.5 mb-5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide text-slate-600">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="inline-block w-3 h-3 rounded-sm bg-emerald-500"></span>
          First-touch credit (% of conversions)
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="inline-block w-3 h-3 rounded-sm bg-slate-500"></span>
          Last-touch credit
        </span>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <% channels.each do |c| %>
          <div>
            <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between mb-2">
              <h3 class="text-sm sm:text-base font-bold text-slate-900"><%= c[:name] %></h3>
              <% if c[:role] == "introducer" %>
                <span class="text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.1em] text-emerald-700 bg-emerald-50 border border-emerald-200 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full">INTRODUCER</span>
              <% elsif c[:role] == "closer" %>
                <span class="text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.1em] text-slate-700 bg-slate-100 border border-slate-300 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full">CLOSER</span>
              <% else %>
                <span class="text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.1em] text-amber-700 bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full">MIXED</span>
              <% end %>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-1.5">
              <div class="w-12 sm:w-16 text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-bold tracking-wider text-emerald-600 shrink-0">FIRST</div>
              <div class="flex-1 h-5 sm:h-6 bg-emerald-50 rounded-sm overflow-hidden">
                <div class="h-full bg-emerald-500 rounded-sm" style="width: <%= (c[:first].to_f / 40 * 100).round %>%;"></div>
              </div>
              <div class="w-10 sm:w-12 text-right text-xs sm:text-sm font-mono font-semibold text-emerald-700 shrink-0"><%= c[:first] %>%</div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
              <div class="w-12 sm:w-16 text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-bold tracking-wider text-slate-500 shrink-0">LAST</div>
              <div class="flex-1 h-5 sm:h-6 bg-slate-100 rounded-sm overflow-hidden">
                <div class="h-full bg-slate-500 rounded-sm" style="width: <%= (c[:last].to_f / 40 * 100).round %>%;"></div>
              </div>
              <div class="w-10 sm:w-12 text-right text-xs sm:text-sm font-mono font-semibold text-slate-700 shrink-0"><%= c[:last] %>%</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        <% end %>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="px-6 sm:px-8 py-5 bg-slate-50 border-t border-slate-200">
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
        <strong class="text-slate-900">Cut the introducers and your closers stop closing.</strong>
        Email and Branded Search look like the heroes under last-click. They're not creating demand &mdash; they're harvesting it. Pause Paid Social and Content for a quarter and you'll see Email and Branded Search ROAS collapse along with them.
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>
  <figcaption class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-3 text-center">
    Illustrative credit split &middot; Pattern (top-funnel introducers under-credited by last-click) consistent with multi-touch attribution case studies
  </figcaption>
</figure>
